import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="US_Gross", color="blue", alpha=0.5, label="US Gross")
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="Worldwide_Gross", color="red", alpha=0.5, label="Worldwide Gross")
    ax.axvline(data["US_Gross"].median(), color="blue", linestyle="--", label="US Gross Median: {:.2f}".format(data["US_Gross"].median()))
    ax.axvline(data["Worldwide_Gross"].median(), color="red", linestyle="--", label="Worldwide Gross Median: {:.2f}".format(data["Worldwide_Gross"].median()))
    ax.set_xlabel("Gross Earnings")
    ax.set_ylabel("Frequency")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?")
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

    sns.histplot(data=data, x="IMDB_Rating", color="blue", alpha=0.5, ax=ax, label="IMDB Rating")

    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Rating")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Running_Time_min', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?')
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (min)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
